   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/military/Ammon_Richard_T1661.abs.pdf">Ammon discusses his 20 years of service with the U.S. Navy on twelve different
            ships. He talks at length about his time on the U.S.S. Kidd, the U.S.S. Bache, and the
            U.S.S. McCaffery. Ammon describes the poor condition of the U.S.S. Bache, the challenge
            of repairing it, its sinking while anchored off Rhodes in 1968, and the work required to
            salvage it. He also describes the relations among sailors aboard the U.S.S. McCaffery
            during the Vietnam War.</abstract>
